  <data name="helpFileAssets" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The file assets are the image and sound files used in the scenes, including the background and characters. The images of characters with transparency are called "sprites". Each sprites and sounds are placed in the same directory, assigned unique IDs, and exported to image and audio HTML elements in the result web pages.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="helpFrameLabel" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The label of frame consists of alphabets, numbers, and underline. It sets up a jumpping target for for path options. It is also the tag for remembering the option the the user selected. For a frame that simply goes to the next frame, it is optional. For a frame the contains path options or wanna be a option of other frames, it is required.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="helpSelectWorkDirectory" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Select a folder as the current working directory. Every sub-directory that contains a xtalk.proj file is listed as a script project. If the related CSS, Images, Scripts files are not found, it prepares for you.</value>
  </data>
